description: Revised application for approval of reserved matters: Design of Initial Stage (Barking Life Long Learning Centre and Garden Housing) of mixed use development for Barking Town Square
decision_conditions:
The permitted development shall not be commenced until details/samples of all facing materials to be used in the development have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and no facing materials shall be used except those so approved.

Reason:
To safeguard the appearance of the development.

The development hereby approved shall only be built in accordance with the interim access arrangement shown on drawing number P110 revision A until a suitable pedestrian route between Ripple Road and the Town Square area is provided. Confirmation of the suitability of this route is to be agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the construction of the extended foyer and cycle store as shown on the above drawing.

Reason:
In the interests of the permeability of the Town Centre by ensuring that a pedestrian route is retained from Ripple Road to the Town Square.

The proposed service area off Axe Street shall not be used for the loading and unloading of vehicles between the hours of 10.30 pm and 7.00 am.

Reason:
In order to protect neighbouring residential occupiers from noise and disturbance at unsocial hours.

No soakaways shall be constructed in contaminated ground.

Reason:
To prevent pollution of groundwater.

The construction of the surface water drainage system shall be carried out in accordance with details submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before the development commences.

Reason:
To prevent pollution of the water environment.

The Lifelong Learning Centre and Garden Housing shall not be occupied until a scheme showing the detailed provision made for cycle parking has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and the agreed scheme for that part of the development has been implemented.

Reason:
In the interests of promoting cycling as a safe, efficient and non-polluting form of transport.

No part of the Lifelong Learning Centre and Garden Housing hereby approved shall be occupied until a plan showing details of the ramped access between Axe Street and the service yard area to include details of any retaining walls has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented.

Reason:
To ensure that the access is suitable for service and other vehicles.

No part of the Lifelong Learning Centre and Garden Housing hereby approved shall be occupied until details of the radar operated traffic lights in the rear service and access road have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented.

Reason:
In the interests of highway safety.

No dwellings on the seventh floor shall be occupied until details of the privacy screens between the units have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented.

Reason:
To protect the privacy of future residents.

Details of the 'green roof' to be installed above the two storey wing of the lifelong learning centre and the 'brown roof' to be installed on the roof of the garden housing as indicated on drawing number P118 revision B together with maintenance schedules shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented prior to the occupation of the respective part of the building on which the green or brown roof is located. 

Reason:
In the interests of biodiversity and in accordance with policy G46 of the Unitary Development Plan.

A scheme showing the provisions to be made for CCTV camera coverage shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and shall be retained unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason:
In the interests of enhancing security and safety and in accordance with policy DE6 of the Unitary Development Plan.

A scheme showing the provisions to be made for external lighting shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and shall be retained unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason:
In the interests of enhancing security and safety and in accordance with policy DE6 of the Unitary Development Plan.

Details of the measures to be undertaken for the protection of the building from vehicle movements within the service yard shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and shall be retained unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason:
In order to protect the building from damage from vehicle movements.

Details of an amended refuse strategy including provision for recyclables shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and retained unless the Local Planning Authority gives written agreement to any variation.

Reason:
To provide satisfactory refuse storage provision in the interests of the appearance of the site and locality and to ensure proper provision is made for recycling in accordance with policy G31 of the Unitary Development Plan.

The rear access road and service area shall only be used in connection with the manoeuvring and circulation of service vehicles and shall not be used at any time for the parking of vehicles otherwise than in conjunction with the servicing of the premises. The access road and service area shall be secured prior to occupation of the building in accordance with details that have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason:
In order that adequate space is maintained to allow service vehicles to safely manoeuvre and in accordance with policy T32 of the Unitary Development Plan.

The development shall not commence until details of the measures to be taken to protect blind and partially sighted people from the V shaped support columns on the north-western side of the building have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason:
In the interests of health and safety.

The development shall not commence until details of the measures to be taken to provide renewable energy within the scheme have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. 

Reason:
In the interests of promoting renewable energy and in accordance with policy G40 of the Unitary Development Plan.
borough: London Borough of Barking and Dagenham
